  "text": "The fact that bilirubin may play a role in the development of AKI in hepatic failure can explain why terlipressin was effective in only 13% of patients with serum bilirubin > 10 mg/ dL (171 μmol/L) compared with 67% of patients with lower serum bilirubin levels according to Nazar et al [CITATION_1] .",
